<dl id="n05054d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05054d">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05054d"> 54(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> night blindness</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> &hellip; <font color="green">[charts]</font> showing how <mark>night-blindness</mark>, or colourblindness, or cataract goes down through families, or how dwarfed stature or short-fingeredness passes from one generation to another. Even a white lock of hair may be a heritage; certainly albinos run in families. <small> <a name="GR25aug23" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#GR25aug23"><cite title="source">The Graphic</cite></a> (25 August 1923) [The Laboratory of the S-Ray] 284</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
